#. type: Title ===
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up HTTPS/SSL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "{project_name} is not set up by default to handle SSL/HTTPS.\n"
"          It is highly recommended that you either enable SSL on the {project_name} server itself or on a reverse proxy in front of the {project_name} server.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "This default behavior is defined by the SSL/HTTPS mode of each {project_name} realm.  This is discussed in more detail in the link:{adminguide_link}[{adminguide_name}], but let's give some context and a brief overview of these modes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#, no-wrap
msgid "external requests"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "{project_name} can run out of the box without SSL so long as you stick to private IP addresses like `localhost`, `127.0.0.1`, `10.0.x.x`, `192.168.x.x`, and `172..16.x.x`.  If you donâ€™t have SSL/HTTPS configured on the server or you try to access {project_name} over HTTP from a non-private IP adress you will get an error."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#, no-wrap
msgid "none"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "{project_name} does not require SSL.  This should really only be used in development when you are playing around with things."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#, no-wrap
msgid "all requests"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "{project_name} requires SSL for all IP addresses."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#| msgid "The next step you have to do is to define and register the client in the {project_name} Admin Console."
msgid "The SSL mode for each realm can be configured in the {project_name} admin console."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#| msgid "To boot the {project_name} server:"
msgid "Enabling SSL/HTTPS for the {project_name} Server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "If you are not using a reverse proxy or load balancer to handle HTTPS traffic for you, you'll need to enable HTTPS for the {project_name} server.  This involves"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Obtaining or generating a keystore that contains the private key and certificate for SSL/HTTP traffic"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Configuring the {project_name} server to use this keypair and certificate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating the Certificate and Java Keystore"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "In order to allow HTTPS connections, you need to obtain a self signed or third-party signed certificate and import it into a Java keystore before you can enable HTTPS in the web container you are deploying the {project_name} Server to."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "====== Self Signed Certificate"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "In development, you will probably not have a third party signed certificate available to test a {project_name} deployment so you'll need to generate a self-signed one using the `keytool` utility that comes with the Java JDK."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ keytool -genkey -alias localhost -keyalg RSA -keystore keycloak.jks -validity 10950\n"
"    Enter keystore password: secret\n"
"    Re-enter new password: secret\n"
"    What is your first and last name?\n"
"    [Unknown]:  localhost\n"
"    What is the name of your organizational unit?\n"
"    [Unknown]:  Keycloak\n"
"    What is the name of your organization?\n"
"    [Unknown]:  Red Hat\n"
"    What is the name of your City or Locality?\n"
"    [Unknown]:  Westford\n"
"    What is the name of your State or Province?\n"
"    [Unknown]:  MA\n"
"    What is the two-letter country code for this unit?\n"
"    [Unknown]:  US\n"
"    Is CN=localhost, OU=Keycloak, O=Test, L=Westford, ST=MA, C=US correct?\n"
"    [no]:  yes\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "You should answer `What is your first and last name ?` question with the DNS name of the machine you're installing the server on.  For testing purposes, `localhost` should be used.  After executing this command, the `keycloak.jks` file will be generated in the same directory as you executed the `keytool` command in."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "If you want a third-party signed certificate, but don't have one, you can obtain one for free at http://www.cacert.org[cacert.org].  You'll have to do a little set up first before doing this though."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "The first thing to do is generate a Certificate Request:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ keytool -certreq -alias yourdomain -keystore keycloak.jks > keycloak.careq\n"
msgstr ""

